===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}} – a cooker for steaming food.

Later {{Han phonetically borrowed}} to represent {{och-l|曾|once already}}. The derivative {{och-l|甑}} refers to the original word. 

In the bronze inscriptions, a decorative {{och-l|*口}} was added, which further evolved into {{och-l|*曰}}.

